CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 23, 1946, pg. 17 reads: "Eighty-Second Milestone - Elder Charles Jackson (center) celebrated his eighty-second birthday recently. Mrs. Vennie Mitchell (left) of the Centre Avenue YMCA Cafeteria provided a cake for the occasion, as Mrs. Thelma Burgess looks on. - Courier Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Charles Jackson cutting birthday cake, with Veenie Mitchell and Thelma Burgess wearing plaid suit jacket, standing in interior of Centre Avenue YMCA with fleur de lis wallpaper
